rComments: She's horrible. She read from the slides, which I could do at home (if it weren't for the stupid quizzes then I would have). She could not keep the classroom quiet and she spoke in a soft monotone voice that made me want to fall asleep. I kinda felt bad for her. =/

She taught my lecture class, and she was not at all interesting.  I think she tried to engage us, but she went right off the slides that we ourselves could pull off of Virtual Campus and go over what's on them.  She seemed a bit lost at times, and had no clue how to use the technical equipment in the classroom.
